    {
        "content": "<p>This partially-ordered-objects notion also reminds me of the proof that, what is it...every locally small category is a quotient of a concrete one, I think that's the statement? Can't remember the author without digging around, but I remember it involves a kind of delicate sorting of the objects by ordinals, so actually eventually a total order. But having a nice partial order related to cardinality or something probably helps you get started.</p>",
        "id": 482707520,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Carlson",
        "timestamp": 1731711381
    }
